A BMI of 25 or higher indicates a person is overweight and people over 30 are considered obese.
You can calculate your BMI here: 1.usa.gov/1D0ZqDv.
For their new study, researchers at Taiwan’s Min-Sheng General Hospital used data collected from a 2007 study that looked at two types of bariatric surgery – gastric bypass and gastrectomy – in treatment procedures for type 3 diabetes in people who were mildly obese.
The average BMI among those who underwent surgery fell from 31 to 24.5 by the end of their fifth year, according to the study.
Meanwhile, the BMI of those who were not given surgical treatment for diabetes remained roughly the same at 29.
